author: Solange Reyner
title: Seattle Times’ high school football rankings, Oct. 22
text:
Class 4A Top 10 
1. Lake Stevens (7-0) 
Beat Mariner, 42-7. Next: Friday vs. Kamiak, 7 p.m.
2. Camas (7-0) 
Beat Union, 51-16. Next: Friday at Mountain View, 7 p.m.
3. Gig Harbor (7-0) 
Beat Olympia, 27-26. Next: Friday vs. Yelm, 7 p.m.
4. Gonzaga Prep (7-0) 
Beat Central Valley, 35-13. Next: Friday vs. Lewis & Clark, 7 p.m.
5. Graham-Kapowsin (7-0) 
Beat Puyallup, 35-13. Next: Thursday vs. Rogers, 7 p.m.
6. Skyline (6-1) 
Beat Bothell, 56-25, Thurs. Next: Friday vs. Inglemoor, 7 p.m.
7. Olympia (6-1) 
Lost to Gig Harbor, 27-26. Next: Friday at Bellarmine Prep, 7 p.m.
8. Richland (6-1) 
Beat Pasco, 35-7. Next: Friday vs. Kamiakin, 7 p.m.
9. Central Valley (5-2) 
Lost to Gonzaga Prep, 35-13. Next: Friday at Ferris, 7 p.m.
10. Kentwood (6-1) 
Beat Kent Meridian, 28-7. Next: Friday vs. Kentlake, 7 p.m.
Class 3A Top 10 
1. Eastside Catholic (7-0) 
Beat O’Dea, 42-14. Next: Idle
2. Bellevue (5-1) 
Beat Liberty, 42-0. Next: Friday at Interlake, 7 p.m.
3. Lincoln (7-0) 
Beat Central Kitsap, 21-0. Next: Friday vs. Wilson, 7 p.m.
4. Sumner (7-0) 
Beat Lakes, 31-24. Next: Friday at Bonney Lake, 7 p.m.
5. Bishop Blanchet (6-1) 
Beat Lakeside, 42-14. Next: Friday at Seattle Prep, 7 p.m.
6. Glacier Peak (6-1) 
Beat Shorecrest, 58-8. Next: Friday vs. Edmonds-Woodway, 7 p.m.
7. O’Dea (5-2) 
Lost to Eastside Cath., 42-14. Next: Friday at Lakeside, 6 p.m.
8. Mt. Spokane (6-1) 
Beat North Central, 56-14. Next: Friday at Rogers, 5 p.m.
9. Auburn Mountainview (5-2) 
Lost to Peninsula, 34-20. Next: Friday vs. Auburn, 7 p.m.
10. Lakes (5-2) 
Lost to Sumner, 31-24. Next: Friday at Enumclaw, 7 p.m.
